title: Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock
description: You are given an array prices where prices[i] is the price of a given stock on the ith day. You want to maximize your profit by choosing a single day to buy one stock and choosing a different day in the future to sell that stock.
example 1: Input: prices = [7,1,5,3,6,4] Output: 5 Explanation: Buy on day 2 (price = 1) and sell on day 5 (price = 6), profit = 6-1 = 5.
example 2: Input: prices = [7,6,4,3,1] Output: 0 Explanation: In this case, no transactions are done, and the max profit is 0.

title: Linked List Cycle
description: Given head, the head of a linked list, determine if the linked list has a cycle in it. If there is a cycle, return true, otherwise return false.
constraint: Constraints: The number of the nodes in the list is in the range [0, 104]. -105 <= Node.val <= 105.

title: Group Anagrams
description: Given an array of strings strs, group the anagrams together. You can return the answer in any order.
constraint: Constraints: 1 <= strs.length <= 104 0 <= strs[i].length <= 100 strs[i] consists of lowercase English letters.

title: Subsets
description: Given an integer array nums of unique elements, return all possible subsets (the power set).
constraint: Constraints: 1 <= nums.length <= 10 -10 <= nums[i] <= 10 All the numbers of nums are unique.

title: Binary Tree Inorder Traversal
description: Given the root of a binary tree, return the inorder traversal of its nodes' values.
constraint: Constraints: The number of nodes in the tree is in the range [0, 100]. -100 <= Node.val <= 100.
